rComments: Don't think the Prof. is nice like he looks like. He is not helpful. Book is more helpful than the Prof.

Feuerverger is a good prof, and the difficulty level of the course and expected amt of student prep is on par with any good stats grad course.  Hints: 1. To understand what is going on in class, you must read the textbook in advance.  2. To do well in the class, you must do the practice finals he'll hand out and aim for about 60%.

The course is tough, but by nature, it should be harder than another stat courses.  You will only able to understand his lectures if you have strong background or do the preparation. Assignments are way too long, the only recommendation is to cut them short as the tough TA is not reading or marking them all.  Overall, he is a nice professor.
approachable, but do not know how to explain
Very poor professor; teaching abilities far below average. Makes fun of students that can not follw. Class notes are completly useless. Avoid Prof. Feuerverger if you can!
Excellent Prof - for such a hard class he made it 'interesting' - and yes - the bell curve did help!

Long and tough final.  Number of assignments were a little excessive.  Lectures were a little vague at times.  Read the book if you want to keep up with them!  Very helpful during office hours.  Nice guy overall.  Just ride the bell curve.
